---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StakeCTA from '../components/StakeCTA.astro';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How much bankroll do I need for Crazy Time?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Bring at least 50 bets worth of bankroll. If betting $2 per round, have at least $100 in your session budget.' } },
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'What bet size should I use in Crazy Time?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Conservative: 1% of session bankroll. Balanced: 2%. Aggressive: 3-5%. Never exceed 5% of your session budget per round.' } },
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'What stop-loss should I set for Crazy Time?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Set a stop-loss of 30-50% of your session bankroll before you start. If you hit it, end the session. Do not reload during the same session.' } },
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Crazy Time Bankroll Strategy — Budget & Bet Sizing Guide 2026"
  description="How to manage your Crazy Time bankroll. Session budgets, stop-loss rules, bet sizing formulas, and the most common mistakes to avoid."
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <h1>Crazy Time Bankroll Strategy 2026</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-300">
      Bankroll management is the most important part of any <a href="/crazy-time-strategy">Crazy Time strategy</a>. It determines how long you play, how many bonus rounds you see, and whether you walk away with something. This guide covers the core rules every player should follow.
    </p>

    <h2>Set a Session Bankroll</h2>
    <p>
      A session bankroll is the fixed amount you bring to a single session. Never add to it mid-session. Keep it separate from your living money. A good starting session bankroll is 50–100 bets worth of your chosen bet size.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use the <a href="/bankroll-calculator">bankroll calculator</a> to calculate your bet size from your session bankroll automatically.
    </p>

    <h2>Bet Sizing Rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Conservative:</strong> 1% of session bankroll per round. Longest sessions, lowest risk.</li>
      <li><strong>Balanced:</strong> 2% per round. Recommended starting point for most players.</li>
      <li><strong>Aggressive:</strong> 3–5% per round. For experienced players with a dedicated bonus hunt budget.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The correct bet size depends on your session bankroll and risk tolerance. Check the <a href="/crazy-time-rtp">RTP breakdown</a> to understand your expected return before choosing a risk level.
    </p>

    <h2>Stop-Loss Rules</h2>
    <p>
      A stop-loss is the maximum amount you are willing to lose in one session. Once hit, you stop — no exceptions. Recommended stop-loss levels:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Conservative: stop at 30% loss of session bankroll</li>
      <li>Balanced: stop at 40% loss</li>
      <li>Aggressive: stop at 50% loss</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Take-Profit Rules</h2>
    <p>
      Setting a take-profit is just as important as a stop-loss. If you hit a bonus round win that doubles your session bankroll, consider stopping. Most players who continue after a big win give it all back. Recommended: stop at 100–150% profit.
    </p>

    <h2>Common Bankroll Mistakes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Not setting a stop-loss before starting</li>
      <li>Increasing bet size to recover losses (Martingale trap)</li>
      <li>Playing with money you cannot afford to lose</li>
      <li>Adding to your session bankroll after busting it</li>
      <li>Playing without a <a href="/session-planner">session plan</a></li>
    </ul>

    <StakeCTA variant="card" text="Play Crazy Time on Stake →" />

    <div class="space-y-4 mt-2">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      {[
        { q: 'How much money do I need to play Crazy Time?', a: 'Minimum: 50 bets. If your bet is $1, bring $50. If your bet is $5, bring $250. More is better — more rounds = more bonus exposure.' },
        { q: 'What is the best stop-loss for Crazy Time?', a: 'For most players, 30–40% of session bankroll is the right stop-loss. This allows enough rounds to hit bonus rounds without risking your full budget.' },
        { q: 'Should I use a flat bet or vary my bets?', a: 'Flat betting is more sustainable. Varying bets based on results or feelings is a form of emotional gambling.' },
        { q: 'Can I split my bankroll across multiple days?', a: 'Yes. Dividing your total budget into daily session amounts is smart bankroll management.' },
        { q: 'What happens if I bust my session bankroll?', a: 'Stop playing for the day. Do not deposit more. Wait for your next scheduled session.' },
      ].map(faq => (
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-100 mb-1 m-0">{faq.q}</p>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm m-0">{faq.a}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-slate-700 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
      <a href="/crazy-time-strategy" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Crazy Time strategy guide</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-rtp" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ RTP breakdown</a>
      <a href="/where-to-play-crazy-time" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Where to play Crazy Time</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-predictor" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Live Crazy Time tracker</a>
    </div>

    <StakeCTA variant="sticky" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
